metadata.name: Vertical World #60
metadata.description:
This artwork is a kind of my inquiry about ambiguous boundaries.
I was a child who liked to draw but always been dissatisfied with my work. Now through coding, I was able to create the "feelings" that I wanted to express. This work is not to imitate a certain landscape or painting style, but simply paint with different brushes, and cooperate with the randomness of the computer.
"I" creates horizontal order, and "computer" creates vertical disorder. My intention is to create
ambiguous visuals in a way that doesn't give specific images, but vague atmosphere.
The meaning is computer-generated and positioned through your eyes.
(It may take more time to render if you using Firefox browser.)

- Press [s] to save png image

Created by haxenfan using p5js.

metadata.name: Ebbs and Flows #31
metadata.description:
"Ebbs and Flows" seamlessly blends dynamic particle movement with a diverse range of color palettes, these color palette’s are reminiscent of influential artists in abstract art. Each piece within this collection offers a visually engaging and ever-evolving composition.

The elements of randomness and controlled chaos are combined to create particle movements across the canvas, guided by mathematical algorithms which generates intricate and unpredictable patterns.

Press [s] to save a PNG file

Press [p] to play or pause animation at anytime

Press [g] to save a 5 second .gif file

For better results use a PC/Laptop

Please be patient for animation to end on its own.

Script, 2023.

metadata.name: Monsoon #85
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: Paper screen door | 明かり障子 (akarishouji) #27
metadata.description:
In a traditional Japanese home, you have sliding walls to separate rooms and create privacy. These are made of wood and washi paper and philtre the light from the sun or moon. 

This is exactly the atmosphere I wanted to convey in this minimalist project. The light of the moon or night lighting plays with the layers of paper in their geometric arrangement. 

The white line represents the part of the wood you touch to open or close the wall. 

Press "Enter" to save the iteration. 

In my usual work, I take everyday objects, materials, etc. and play with them. For this series, I inserted texture of polystyrene.

All graphical elements, colours, and random arrangements were created by code using P5.js, texture patterns are embedded in the code. 

6 colours available : red, yellow, green, blue, white, pink.

@Yomu Oyashi August 2022

metadata.name: Alien Form #44
metadata.description:
"Alien Form" is an animated generative real time 3D sculpture. 

CONTROLS

KEYS:

- V: Render an arbitrary view (object view angle variation) on each key press
- S: Save a png file
- R: Reset/reload
- SPACEBAR: Toggle animation (on/off)

MOUSE:

- Click: Toggle animation (on/off) (the same as the SPACEBAR)

----
Made with p5js

© Sep. 2023  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: Egos #109
metadata.description:
"Art comes to people from God. Now it is in the will of man to create. therefore, art is the representation of the feelings of the free individual. The old must be erased and the new reigned." 
 Charles Baudelaire

 In this collection, geometric forms created by symbolic individuals are examined.

* You have to be patient for the animations to work properly.
* Save image: press 's' to save the current image as png.

* Owners can get 6 free per person for their support in my previous three collections. 
 Among the new collectors, 5 works will be open to access.
 20 percent of the royalty will belong to the minters.
